05/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A recent poll by the Partner.ms agency shows the ultranationalist Serbian Radical Party (SRS) has the strongest support of any one party in Serbia. According to results published Monday (4 July), 31.5 per cent of respondents said they would vote for SRS, if the elections were held now. President Boris Tadic's Democratic Party was second with 25.7 per cent, followed by the Power of Serbia -- a movement led by the businessman Bogoljub Karic -- with 15.9 per cent. The ruling Democratic Party of Serbia was fourth with 11.2 per cent. (B92, Beta - 04/07/05)
